# PC/Mobile 분리
	## PC 
		- ie8, chrome, safari

		- html4.01 Transitional
			<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
			
			<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" />
			
			
		- viewport
			HTML5 introduced a method to let web designers take control over the viewport(the user's visible area of a web page), through the <meta> tag  ???	
			<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no" />



		- mark up common rule
			- closed empty elements
				HTML5 dose not require empty elements to be closed. But I want stricter validation, and need to make my document readable by XML parser, so I close all HTML elements properly.
				
			- lowercase tag 




